[iQIYI]

8
00:00:17,480 --> 00:00:19,450
[Present]

9
00:00:19,550 --> 00:00:26,510
♫Never met anyone who could make me understand this word♫

10
00:00:27,880 --> 00:00:34,780
♫But when I met you, my heart started beating fast♫

11
00:00:36,010 --> 00:00:43,180
♫You’re the only one in my heart who could make me feel this way♫

12
00:00:44,380 --> 00:00:50,910
♫This long-awaitied moment is now over♫

13
00:00:52,080 --> 00:00:56,350
♫From now on, my heart and soul will be yours for the rest of my life♫

14
00:00:56,350 --> 00:00:59,680
♫Always have each other, never let go♫

15
00:01:00,050 --> 00:01:04,750
♫Trust in me ‘cause I’ll be by your side♫

16
00:01:04,750 --> 00:01:09,780
♫Hold my hand, Baby♫

17
00:01:09,780 --> 00:01:12,980
[Desires in the Wind]

18
00:01:13,700 --> 00:01:17,780
[Previously]
When everything is over, let’s go see the snow in Madelin together.

19
00:01:18,130 --> 00:01:19,400
That’s the flare from the resort.

20
00:01:19,500 --> 00:01:20,700
We must get out of here.

21
00:01:23,930 --> 00:01:25,050
Where’s Miss Blew?

22
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:27,100
She’s been taken.

23
00:01:28,210 --> 00:01:29,360
I already turned it on.

24
00:01:29,560 --> 00:01:31,300
They’ll probably come swarming here soon.

25
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:32,400
Is it a trap?

26
00:01:32,930 --> 00:01:33,729
I know.

27
00:01:33,860 --> 00:01:35,700
But even if it’s a trap, I still have to go.

28
00:01:36,060 --> 00:01:38,410
Grace, Helena is gone.

29
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:41,460
I’ll take care of her myself.

30
00:01:48,860 --> 00:01:50,150
Miss Blew.

31
00:01:51,700 --> 00:01:53,080
Miss Blew.

32
00:01:57,460 --> 00:01:58,560
Miss Vayo.

33
00:02:08,900 --> 00:02:09,900
I’m okay.

34
00:02:21,730 --> 00:02:23,380
You look so much like me.

35
00:03:15,600 --> 00:03:18,010
I know you’re not a bad person.

36
00:03:20,730 --> 00:03:23,180
I don’t know what you’ve been through.

37
00:03:24,900 --> 00:03:29,110
But your eyes, they tell me you don’t want to do this.

38
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:31,200
I can help you.

39
00:03:36,660 --> 00:03:38,260
Grace is using you.

40
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:44,350
If anything happens, the first one to die is you.

41
00:03:46,460 --> 00:03:47,500
It’s still not too late.

42
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:51,380
I know you don’t want to do this.

43
00:03:51,460 --> 00:03:52,530
I’m sorry, Your Highness.

44
00:03:54,100 --> 00:03:55,880
I just want to survive.

45
00:03:56,730 --> 00:03:58,600
I don’t want to do this anymore.

46
00:04:02,530 --> 00:04:09,910
If you help me, I promise I will tell Father to grant you a pardon.

47
00:04:10,130 --> 00:04:12,450
I don’t think I could help you that much.

48
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:15,150
Grace’s people are guarding around this place.

49
00:04:20,860 --> 00:04:26,150
Swap places with me. I’ll run away and get the police here

50
00:04:26,910 --> 00:04:30,510
to arrest Grace and all the traitors.

51
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:02,210
I promise I’ll come back for you.

52
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:05,280
Just try to stall for time as best as you can.

53
00:05:45,930 --> 00:05:47,210
Miss Vayo.

54
00:05:57,100 --> 00:05:59,550
I’m glad you’re safe.

55
00:06:01,750 --> 00:06:02,850
Miss Vayo!

56
00:06:22,130 --> 00:06:23,350
Miss Vayo!

57
00:06:25,930 --> 00:06:27,250
Miss Vayo!

58
00:06:28,730 --> 00:06:29,600
Please stay with me.

59
00:06:29,930 --> 00:06:30,730
Miss Vayo!

60
00:06:32,330 --> 00:06:33,580
Miss Vayo!

61
00:06:36,260 --> 00:06:38,860
Miss Vayo!

62
00:06:53,060 --> 00:06:54,909
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

63
00:07:07,530 --> 00:07:08,360
How’s she?

64
00:07:09,500 --> 00:07:10,600
Fai just told me.

65
00:07:10,730 --> 00:07:12,110
I’ve been worried sick.

66
00:07:12,360 --> 00:07:13,460
Still unconcious.

67
00:07:16,730 --> 00:07:19,310
Why did you have to help her run away from the hospital?

68
00:07:19,400 --> 00:07:21,980
How could you let her do something dangerous like that

69
00:07:24,200 --> 00:07:25,960
You know how stubborn she is.

70
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:29,180
If we didn’t help her, she would’ve found a way to escape anyway.

71
00:07:35,530 --> 00:07:36,460
I don’t get it.

72
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:44,480
Why did she have to risk her life like that, all just to protect a woman–a princess?

73
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:48,060
It’s because of love.

74
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:53,810
She’s probably found someone she truly loves.

75
00:08:00,760 --> 00:08:02,410
Is it even possible?

76
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:09,650
Lom and Princess Blew, do you really think it could happen?

77
00:08:11,130 --> 00:08:13,000
But isn’t it something to be proud of?

78
00:08:14,130 --> 00:08:18,000
Once in her life, she has sacrificed herself to protect the person she loves.

79
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:23,400
Miss Blew probably feels it too.

80
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:29,960
So, how’s Miss Blew?

81
00:08:41,659 --> 00:08:44,310
How are you, my daughter?

82
00:08:46,900 --> 00:08:48,180
Father.

83
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:54,980
Karel.

84
00:08:56,980 --> 00:08:58,950
All traitors have been executed.

85
00:08:58,950 --> 00:09:01,180
Please rest assured, Sister.

86
00:09:01,860 --> 00:09:07,500
I’m such a fool to never know how much danger you had to go through.

87
00:09:09,730 --> 00:09:11,860
I’m sorry I couldn’t protect you.

88
00:09:18,700 --> 00:09:20,300
It’s not your fault, Father.

89
00:09:30,860 --> 00:09:32,860
Thank God you’re safe.

90
00:09:38,410 --> 00:09:46,550
What about Miss Vayo? Is she all right?

91
00:09:48,900 --> 00:09:52,900
She’s still unconscious. But overall, she’s safe now.

92
00:09:56,530 --> 00:10:05,980
For your own safety, I’ll take you back to Madelin immediately
after the doctor’s examination tomorrow.

93
00:10:09,560 --> 00:10:10,810
Tomorrow…

94
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:45,980
Lom.

95
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:47,400
How are you?

96
00:10:48,100 --> 00:10:49,450
How are you?

97
00:10:53,930 --> 00:10:56,350
I knew you all would be here.

98
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,500
Geez, this brat.

99
00:11:09,800 --> 00:11:11,080
Where’s Miss Blew?

100
00:11:18,530 --> 00:11:24,300
She just…got discharged from the hospital this morning.

101
00:11:27,300 --> 00:11:30,100
Can I go see her then?

102
00:11:30,730 --> 00:11:31,530
No.

103
00:11:35,460 --> 00:11:36,930
You still need physical therapy.

104
00:11:38,060 --> 00:11:39,700
The doctor said you can’t leave yet.

105
00:11:41,760 --> 00:11:45,510
You won’t make it in time anyway.

106
00:11:50,900 --> 00:11:51,860
What do you mean?

107
00:11:56,660 --> 00:11:58,960
Miss Blew will fly back to Madelin this afternoon.

108
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:10,400
She came to visit you this morning but you were still unconscious.

109
00:12:12,760 --> 00:12:14,700
So, she’s left you this letter instead.

110
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:31,810
By the time you are reading this letter, I would have been long gone.

111
00:12:34,060 --> 00:12:36,060
I'm sorry I didn't stay to bid you farewell.

112
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:46,980
Unfortunately, a gravely ill matter of treason has required my urgent return to Madelin.

113
00:12:51,130 --> 00:12:53,600
Thank you for still being alive.

114
00:12:59,930 --> 00:13:16,110
Thank you...for always staying by my side and protecting me.

115
00:13:22,500 --> 00:13:25,500
Thank you for getting hurt and risking your life for me.

116
00:13:29,130 --> 00:13:34,780
I now realise how unconditional your love is.

117
00:13:36,110 --> 00:13:39,250
It is the most precious thing in my life.

118
00:13:40,110 --> 00:13:46,380
I am so blessed to be loved by the person whom I share the same feelings with.

119
00:13:57,500 --> 00:14:02,980
Being apart this time, I do not know when we will meet again.

120
00:14:04,860 --> 00:14:13,350
But whenever I can feel the wind blow, I will always think of you.

121
00:14:18,530 --> 00:14:19,880
I love you.

122
00:14:47,160 --> 00:14:49,710
May life treat you well.

123
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:54,980
I shall do my best to carry out my duty here too.

124
00:15:51,950 --> 00:15:56,780
♫It’s okay, you don’t have to say it now♫

125
00:15:59,650 --> 00:16:04,610
♫I want you to take your time♫

126
00:16:06,150 --> 00:16:09,880
♫Those things we’ve been through♫

127
00:16:10,280 --> 00:16:14,880
♫Those time we’ve spent together♫

128
00:16:14,880 --> 00:16:20,050
♫I still remember them vividly♫

129
00:16:22,980 --> 00:16:28,050
♫For all that we've been through♫

130
00:16:30,710 --> 00:16:35,750
♫Be it good or bad♫

131
00:16:37,480 --> 00:16:41,210
♫It made me realise♫

132
00:16:41,210 --> 00:16:52,810
♫That having you here means so much to me♫

133
00:16:52,810 --> 00:17:01,010
♫Stay with me, please don’t go♫

134
00:17:01,510 --> 00:17:07,750
♫All my heart, there’s only you♫

135
00:17:08,349 --> 00:17:16,380
♫Stay with me, now and forever♫

136
00:17:16,380 --> 00:17:21,480
♫Let there be only me and you

137
00:17:22,650 --> 00:17:27,250
♫please don’t go♫

138
00:18:06,900 --> 00:18:08,750
Look after Madelin for me.

139
00:18:09,500 --> 00:18:12,300
Don’t say that. You must go back to Madelin, Princess.

140
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:19,010
But for now, I want to stay here forever.

141
00:18:43,360 --> 00:18:45,100
I knew it. There you are.

142
00:18:48,210 --> 00:18:52,980
It’s been over a month. Your leg is as good as new now.

143
00:18:54,730 --> 00:18:57,560
But the wound in your heart is probably not healed yet.

144
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:01,700
Are you coming from Surat just to annoy me?

145
00:19:03,260 --> 00:19:05,110
She’s worried about you.

146
00:19:11,360 --> 00:19:17,350
Hey, Uncle Thit said King Arthur has sent us an invitation to visit Madelin.

147
00:19:17,350 --> 00:19:19,610
He’d like to hold a thank you party for us.

148
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:27,360
Really? I have no idea.

149
00:19:29,100 --> 00:19:32,780
How would you? Secluding yourself from the world like this.

150
00:19:33,250 --> 00:19:35,610
No phone calls or talking to anyone.

151
00:19:36,400 --> 00:19:37,200
Yeah.

152
00:19:41,330 --> 00:19:43,930
This is it, Sis. If you miss her, just go see her.

153
00:19:49,330 --> 00:19:53,410
I want to, but I’m also scared.

154
00:19:56,360 --> 00:19:58,650
Everything is not the same anymore.

155
00:20:00,960 --> 00:20:03,730
And you chose to stay with your own fear instead?

156
00:20:08,710 --> 00:20:10,400
Don’t be a chicken, Lieutenant.

157
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:13,760
You hardly blink when you fight those criminals.

158
00:20:14,530 --> 00:20:16,400
Why don’t you just give it a try?

159
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:18,500
If it doesn’t work out, then you can just move on.

160
00:20:19,700 --> 00:20:21,160
We’ll go with you too.

161
00:20:21,760 --> 00:20:26,750
No matter what it’d turn out to be, you’ll always have us to support you.

162
00:20:42,800 --> 00:20:46,650
Miss Vayo has already accepted our invitation to join the party?

163
00:20:47,330 --> 00:20:51,050
Yes. Father has just received the news a while ago.

164
00:20:56,130 --> 00:21:00,280
Aren’t you happy? You’ll get to see the person who saved your life.

165
00:21:03,700 --> 00:21:04,500
I am.

166
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:06,760
But I’ve just been assigned a new duty.

167
00:21:07,060 --> 00:21:08,560
I’m worried I mightn't be able to make preparations in time.

168
00:21:10,700 --> 00:21:11,780
I understand.

169
00:21:12,380 --> 00:21:16,510
After this treason matter is done, you have to prepare yourself for taking the throne.

170
00:21:19,500 --> 00:21:23,480
Can you take care of the guest reception for me then?

171
00:21:24,060 --> 00:21:27,660
Of course, I’ll arrange for everything and take care of the guests for you.

172
00:22:13,250 --> 00:22:14,700
It’s all right.

173
00:22:17,800 --> 00:22:20,110
I notice the light is still on.

174
00:22:21,500 --> 00:22:22,760
Are you still working?

175
00:22:24,730 --> 00:22:25,750
Yes, Father.

176
00:22:33,660 --> 00:22:40,860
Seeing you like this, I’m more confident you’ll take Madelin into great prosperity–much more than when under my reign.

177
00:22:43,700 --> 00:22:46,100
I could never compete with you, Father.

178
00:22:52,860 --> 00:22:58,260
Would it be possible to reconsider your decision to step down from the throne, Father?

179
00:23:00,960 --> 00:23:01,760
Why?

180
00:23:03,960 --> 00:23:06,500
I believe you’re still in good health.

181
00:23:07,800 --> 00:23:09,760
Why step down so soon?

182
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:18,010
The recent treason matter has created a wave of worry among Madelin people.

183
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:22,510
Having a new leader would help enhance the state of affairs.

184
00:23:25,660 --> 00:23:29,750
Then, after I become Queen

185
00:23:30,730 --> 00:23:35,980
and once Karel is ready, can I give up the throne to him?

186
00:23:37,760 --> 00:23:39,700
Why would you do that?

187
00:23:40,460 --> 00:23:42,560
Karel will always be there to help you anyway.

188
00:23:45,860 --> 00:23:58,280
Actually, it’s not just the throne that I want to give up, but also my royal title.

189
00:24:00,060 --> 00:24:06,210
Giving up royal titles is only possible when the royal member has committed a serious crime

190
00:24:07,250 --> 00:24:09,880
or decided to marry a commoner.

191
00:24:10,750 --> 00:24:15,480
I have absolutely no doubt you will never violate any of those rules.

192
00:24:16,150 --> 00:24:18,410
What’s that matter?

193
00:24:20,960 --> 00:24:21,930
Nothing, Father.

194
00:24:24,300 --> 00:24:26,950
Then, never mention it to me again.

195
00:24:28,100 --> 00:24:37,050
And never forget that your duty as the crown princess always comes first and foremost.

196
00:24:42,500 --> 00:24:43,300
Yes, Father.

197
00:25:43,700 --> 00:25:46,480
Welcome, King Arthur is waiting inside.

198
00:26:05,730 --> 00:26:07,100
Please be at ease.

199
00:26:11,700 --> 00:26:13,510
I hope you are well now, Miss Vayo.

200
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:16,100
Yes, Your Highness.

201
00:26:22,130 --> 00:26:24,500
Isn’t Princess Catherine with you too, Your Highness?

202
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:28,150
She is engaged in her duty and won’t be able to make her presence.

203
00:26:28,150 --> 00:26:30,910
But she promises she’ll join us at dinner.

204
00:26:36,860 --> 00:26:39,050
You must have been exhausted from the trip.

205
00:26:39,260 --> 00:26:41,300
Please get some rest and make yourself comfortable.

206
00:26:47,360 --> 00:26:48,550
This way, please.

207
00:27:08,260 --> 00:27:13,010
Hey, after putting our bags in the room, should we go take a walk in the garden? In case we might run into Miss Blew.

208
00:27:13,930 --> 00:27:19,180
This place is so big. Even if we're in the same place–if she doesn’t want us to see her–then you won’t find her.

209
00:27:19,360 --> 00:27:22,350
She must be busy. You’ll definitely see her this evening, right?

210
00:27:22,530 --> 00:27:24,950
Yeah. If you two are meant to be, then it will be.

211
00:27:43,460 --> 00:27:45,160
Princess Catherine will make her presence.

212
00:28:14,160 --> 00:28:15,700
Please be at ease.

213
00:28:36,330 --> 00:28:39,550
I’m glad to see you again, Your Highness.

214
00:28:41,660 --> 00:28:46,680
Welcome to Madelin, Miss Vayo. Is there anything you find lacking here?

215
00:28:49,130 --> 00:28:53,810
Prince Karel has assigned someone to take excellent care of me and my family, Your Highness.

216
00:28:54,860 --> 00:28:56,100
Then, I’m relieved.

217
00:28:59,300 --> 00:29:00,180
So…

218
00:29:00,180 --> 00:29:02,210
Has the trip exhausted you, Miss Fah?

219
00:29:02,530 --> 00:29:06,280
Not at all, Your Highness. May I ask how you are doing?

220
00:29:06,400 --> 00:29:07,260
Very well, thank you.

221
00:29:09,730 --> 00:29:11,300
Miss Nam, how are you doing?

222
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:14,380
I’m good, Your Highness.

223
00:29:56,900 --> 00:30:02,180
I’d like to express my sincere gratitude to all of you for helping my beloved daughter.

224
00:30:03,150 --> 00:30:05,150
Especially to you, Miss Vayo.

225
00:30:10,330 --> 00:30:13,730
If there’s anything I could do to repay you, please don’t hesitate to say it.

226
00:30:19,700 --> 00:30:25,580
Would you kindly grant me permission to make a scoop on your coronation ceremony, Your Highness?

227
00:30:26,500 --> 00:30:29,510
Of course, the ceremony will be held next month.

228
00:30:31,300 --> 00:30:34,560
Does that mean the princess will become Queen after that?

229
00:30:35,900 --> 00:30:37,750
I’m still the same as before.

230
00:30:41,860 --> 00:30:45,080
Then, on behalf of the Watinwanich family,

231
00:30:45,080 --> 00:30:47,910
please allow me to take this opportunity to congratulate you in advance, Princess Blew.

232
00:30:52,600 --> 00:30:54,110
No, not Princess.

233
00:30:59,500 --> 00:31:01,560
It’s Queen Catherine.

234
00:31:04,330 --> 00:31:07,150
Congratulations, Your Majesty.

235
00:31:10,760 --> 00:31:13,980
Miss Vayo, please call me like you used to.

236
00:31:15,460 --> 00:31:18,480
I wouldn’t dare doing that, Your Majesty.

237
00:31:19,050 --> 00:31:23,180
Because now, things are not the same anymore.

238
00:31:35,930 --> 00:31:41,610
Once you become Queen, it’s time to find someone to stay by your side.

239
00:31:42,760 --> 00:31:46,650
Have you given any thought to your marriage?

240
00:31:47,260 --> 00:31:50,950
Or is there any prince you’ve been having your eye on lately?

241
00:31:53,560 --> 00:31:55,100
I’ve hardly given it any thought, Father.

242
00:31:56,250 --> 00:32:04,250
Then, do it now. What about Prince Henry? He seems to be interested in you.

243
00:32:05,060 --> 00:32:08,680
Let’s not talk about this now, Father. It’d only bore our guests.

244
00:33:41,160 --> 00:33:44,750
You and your family wish to move up your schedule and will return to Thailand tomorrow?

245
00:33:45,260 --> 00:33:46,060
Yes, Your Highness.

246
00:33:47,700 --> 00:33:50,950
Is something bothering your mind? You can be honest with me.

247
00:33:51,200 --> 00:33:54,150
We’ve received outstanding hospitality at the palace, Your Highness.

248
00:33:54,150 --> 00:33:58,580
My family and I are very grateful, but we’d rather not impose on you any further.

249
00:33:58,580 --> 00:34:01,480
Besides, my sisters have some work to attend to.

250
00:34:02,760 --> 00:34:08,909
What a pity then. Is there anything you’d like to do before you leave? I’ll have it taken care of.

251
00:34:12,860 --> 00:34:19,010
I haven’t had a chance to speak with Princess Catherine since I came here, Your Highness.

252
00:34:20,310 --> 00:34:22,679
I’d like to say goodbye to her before I leave.

253
00:34:24,659 --> 00:34:27,050
No problem. I’ll let her know.

254
00:35:22,700 --> 00:35:24,800
Karel said you want to see me.

255
00:35:29,760 --> 00:35:33,610
Yes, I want to see you–

256
00:35:35,010 --> 00:35:37,150
the one that’s not Princess Catherine.

257
00:35:46,700 --> 00:35:48,000
I’m leaving.

258
00:35:53,460 --> 00:35:54,360
I know.

259
00:35:59,600 --> 00:36:05,050
In the end, we’re like a story with no happy ending.

260
00:36:06,510 --> 00:36:11,750
The princess always ends up with the prince.

261
00:36:15,600 --> 00:36:22,050
What happens between us, please think of it as just a dream.

262
00:36:25,500 --> 00:36:34,410
It’s time to forget everything, and wake up from that dream.

263
00:36:39,930 --> 00:36:41,700
Can you really forget it?

264
00:36:48,360 --> 00:36:49,950
I won’t forget it.

265
00:36:51,100 --> 00:36:52,800
I’ll keep it in my heart.

266
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:04,480
What can I do for us to be Wind and Phatpha again?

267
00:37:07,400 --> 00:37:10,050
I’m afraid I can’t put my own happiness over my duty.

268
00:37:11,260 --> 00:37:13,010
I’m obliged to my responsibilities.

269
00:37:16,130 --> 00:37:18,530
I do hope you’ll live a happy life from now on.

270
00:37:23,130 --> 00:37:24,530
I don’t think I can do that.

271
00:37:33,360 --> 00:37:39,380
Just think of me as if I were dead.

272
00:37:42,100 --> 00:37:49,550
That day when Helena died, Phatpha also left your world and would never return.

273
00:37:57,700 --> 00:37:59,510
It feels like you’re breaking up with me.

274
00:38:09,730 --> 00:38:11,280
I love you.

275
00:38:16,800 --> 00:38:19,400
Goodbye, Princess Catherine.

276
00:38:56,160 --> 00:39:01,680
I love you too, Miss Vayo.

277
00:39:23,330 --> 00:39:27,550
If there’s a chance, come to Madelin again. You’re always welcome here.

278
00:39:27,960 --> 00:39:31,110
Madelin is so beautiful. I will definitely come back, Your Highness.

279
00:39:31,860 --> 00:39:36,910
Please come visit Thailand again if you have a chance, Your Highness. You’re more than welcome to stay at my farm.

280
00:39:38,060 --> 00:39:41,350
Or at my hotel, Your Highness.

281
00:39:41,560 --> 00:39:43,410
Of course, I’ll certainly be there.

282
00:39:44,130 --> 00:39:46,050
We’ll take our leave then, Your Highness.

283
00:41:02,530 --> 00:41:04,960
Is she still in her bedroom?

284
00:41:05,560 --> 00:41:10,680
Yes, Your Highness. The princess hasn’t left her room since yesterday.

285
00:41:16,860 --> 00:41:22,450
Would you like me to tell her that you’re here, Your Highness?

286
00:41:25,330 --> 00:41:26,380
No need.

287
00:42:11,130 --> 00:42:16,550
Since we came back from Thailand, it seems you’ve changed a lot.

288
00:42:20,100 --> 00:42:21,650
How so?

289
00:42:22,600 --> 00:42:26,550
It’s as if you had left your smile and happiness in Thailand.

290
00:42:31,660 --> 00:42:33,160
Is it because of Miss Vayo?

291
00:42:36,530 --> 00:42:38,380
What does she have to do with this?

292
00:42:44,100 --> 00:42:45,950
I know you two are in love.

293
00:42:46,000 --> 00:42:48,180
Watch your words, Karel.

294
00:42:48,580 --> 00:42:52,350
If Father happens to hear it, he might be furious.

295
00:42:52,680 --> 00:42:58,110
I need to focus on the upcoming coronation ceremony.

296
00:42:58,110 --> 00:43:00,910
I don’t have time for anything nonsense.

297
00:43:08,900 --> 00:43:15,180
You can lie to me but you can never fool your own heart.

298
00:43:26,100 --> 00:43:28,380
I’ve never lied to my heart.

299
00:43:29,410 --> 00:43:36,250
But I can’t just throw away my duty and responsibility as a crown princess.

300
00:43:37,860 --> 00:43:42,280
จุดที่พี่ยืนอยู่I am standing at a point where I cannot follow my own heart.

301
00:43:45,560 --> 00:43:50,480
I can’t fall in love, even when I’ve found that person I truly love.

302
00:43:59,300 --> 00:44:02,900
So, you admit that you love her.

303
00:44:15,900 --> 00:44:20,010
Yes, I love Miss Vayo.

304
00:44:22,360 --> 00:44:24,880
Then, just follow your heart.

305
00:44:32,760 --> 00:44:37,880
Ever since I can remember, you’ve always done everything for our family–

306
00:44:41,300 --> 00:44:44,980
devoting yourself to the people of Madelin.

307
00:44:47,480 --> 00:44:51,580
Never once have you done anything for your own needs or happiness.

308
00:44:57,000 --> 00:45:01,680
So this time, I’m begging you to please listen to your heart and do something for yourself.

309
00:45:05,560 --> 00:45:12,610
Even if I want to, Father will not allow it.

310
00:45:15,160 --> 00:45:20,150
I never hesitate if I have to choose between the throne and the person I love.

311
00:45:30,300 --> 00:45:36,010
But I don’t want to disappoint Father. I don’t want to break his heart.

312
00:45:37,200 --> 00:45:40,150
Father won’t be sad or disappointed forever.

313
00:45:41,660 --> 00:45:47,310
But if you make a wrong decision now, you might be sorry for the rest of your life.

314
00:46:05,130 --> 00:46:09,080
Besides, Madelin still has me.

315
00:46:10,810 --> 00:46:15,280
I’ll use this chance to steal the throne from you.

316
00:46:24,600 --> 00:46:26,000
Thank you, Karel.

317
00:46:36,100 --> 00:46:37,780
What did you just say?

318
00:46:38,130 --> 00:46:40,380
You’re going to give up the throne?

319
00:46:47,260 --> 00:46:57,610
Yes, Father. I’m going to give up my royal title too, for I don’t deserve to be the Queen of Madelin–

320
00:46:59,560 --> 00:47:02,080
because I’m in love with a commoner.

321
00:47:05,530 --> 00:47:07,580
I’m in love with Miss Vayo.

322
00:47:10,200 --> 00:47:11,760
You love who?

323
00:47:17,930 --> 00:47:19,600
I love Miss Vayo, Father.

324
00:47:21,860 --> 00:47:24,980
But you’ve barely known her.

325
00:47:30,130 --> 00:47:36,650
Even so, we’ve been through life and death together for countless times.

326
00:47:38,400 --> 00:47:40,750
She risked her life for me.

327
00:47:42,900 --> 00:47:45,680
And I have absolutely no doubt in this love.

328
00:47:52,130 --> 00:47:56,650
How could you be so negligent to your own duty as the crown princess?

329
00:47:58,500 --> 00:48:00,130
Please forgive me, Father.

330
00:48:02,800 --> 00:48:07,450
But I’m afraid I won’t be able to live without her.

331
00:48:09,600 --> 00:48:12,110
Please grant me your approval, Father.

332
00:48:15,060 --> 00:48:20,480
Is she more important to you than Madelin?

333
00:48:28,660 --> 00:48:29,460
Yes.

334
00:48:32,260 --> 00:48:36,760
More than the royal title and all the money you’d gain from it?

335
00:48:38,900 --> 00:48:39,700
Yes.

336
00:48:42,330 --> 00:48:46,750
No matter what I say, you will still choose this path, won’t you?

337
00:48:50,730 --> 00:48:51,530
Yes.

338
00:48:57,930 --> 00:49:03,880
Fine! I now pronounce Princess Catherine a commoner. She must leave the palace immediately

339
00:49:03,900 --> 00:49:08,680
and shall not take a single valuable item with her!

340
00:49:26,530 --> 00:49:29,850
I’ve arranged a quiet and peaceful place for you to stay.

341
00:49:29,930 --> 00:49:31,910
Thank you for helping me, Karel.

342
00:49:33,500 --> 00:49:35,500
What are you going to do next?

343
00:49:37,400 --> 00:49:41,610
Once I’m able to settle down, I’ll fly to Thailand to see Miss Vayo.

344
00:49:43,800 --> 00:49:46,950
About Father, you don’t need to worry much.

345
00:49:47,210 --> 00:49:51,050
He loves you so dearly. He won’t stay angry for long.

346
00:50:39,460 --> 00:50:43,080
The first snow should be coming soon.

347
00:50:44,860 --> 00:50:50,380
Once everything is over, let’s go see the snow in Madelin together.

348
00:51:18,200 --> 00:51:21,610
It’s our first snow. Are you watching?

349
00:51:25,530 --> 00:51:28,310
Yes, I am.

350
00:52:02,880 --> 00:52:07,450
Is the snow here beautiful like I’ve told you?

351
00:52:08,730 --> 00:52:09,530
Miss Blew.

352
00:52:12,730 --> 00:52:17,380
I mean Princess Catherine. What are you doing here, Your Highness?

353
00:52:17,660 --> 00:52:22,610
You don’t need to use royal terms with me. I’m no longer a princess.

354
00:52:23,960 --> 00:52:25,100
What do you mean?

355
00:52:29,530 --> 00:52:34,450
Father punished me. He removed my royal title

356
00:52:34,460 --> 00:52:36,980
and banished me from the palace.

357
00:52:38,160 --> 00:52:42,880
What have you done? Why is the punishment so serious?

358
00:52:44,460 --> 00:52:49,910
I just told him…that I love you.

359
00:52:58,860 --> 00:53:04,150
Now, I can finally cross the line to be with you…as I promised.

360
00:53:24,860 --> 00:53:32,880
From now on, there’ll be just Lom and Blew–no more Princess.

361
00:53:37,660 --> 00:53:39,180
I love you, Blew.

362
00:53:39,930 --> 00:53:41,580
I love you too, Lom.

363
00:54:33,200 --> 00:54:35,650
When are you going back to Thailand?

364
00:54:39,860 --> 00:54:43,800
At first, I planned to leave after your coronation ceremony was done.

365
00:54:44,660 --> 00:54:46,810
But now, I’ve changed my mind.

366
00:54:47,860 --> 00:54:49,780
I’m going to take you back with me too.

367
00:54:51,060 --> 00:54:56,710
But now that I’m not a princess anymore, will everyone be okay with it?

368
00:54:57,460 --> 00:55:01,850
I’m completely broke. What else can I do if I go to Thailand?

369
00:55:03,160 --> 00:55:05,410
You can make me happy.

370
00:55:07,860 --> 00:55:12,610
Don’t worry, I’ll look after you for the rest of my life.

371
00:55:21,600 --> 00:55:23,780
I never thought this day would come true.

372
00:55:25,930 --> 00:55:30,110
Neither do I. It’s like a dream.

373
00:55:32,100 --> 00:55:34,050
But a beautiful one, isn’t it?

374
00:56:29,360 --> 00:56:31,060
I’m sorry.

375
00:56:33,700 --> 00:56:35,610
I want to make it right first.

376
00:56:38,400 --> 00:56:39,980
You know what I mean, right?

377
00:57:11,460 --> 00:57:12,360
Quite sweet.

378
00:57:15,700 --> 00:57:17,560
Have you heard from Lom, Din?

379
00:57:17,760 --> 00:57:19,300
I’m worried sick about her–

380
00:57:20,060 --> 00:57:23,050
being heartbroken and staying afar from home like that.

381
00:57:24,160 --> 00:57:27,510
If I still can’t get ahold of her, I’m going to report a missing person.

382
00:57:29,330 --> 00:57:33,300
I tried calling but her phone is off. She’s probably trying to hold it together.

383
00:57:37,730 --> 00:57:42,950
Anyway, I’ll tell Fah to ask Prince Karel if he could help.

384
00:57:45,600 --> 00:57:52,550
My dear Lom, she must be crying her heart out right now. Right, Din?

385
00:57:52,730 --> 00:57:55,810
I already sent Princess to where Miss Lom is staying.

386
00:57:56,460 --> 00:57:58,930
Does that mean they are both together now, Your Highness?

387
00:58:01,510 --> 00:58:03,410
Finally, my sister can be happy.

388
00:58:03,700 --> 00:58:06,910
Thanks to you for letting me know beforehand.

389
00:58:27,800 --> 00:58:32,580
Is your name Blew, Sister? You look so beautiful like a princess.

390
00:58:33,900 --> 00:58:35,080
Thank you.

391
00:58:35,300 --> 00:58:40,910
Wind said you’re the person she loves.

392
00:58:42,200 --> 00:58:46,750
You’re Wind’s princess. Wind wants you to join her at breakfast.

393
00:58:48,400 --> 00:58:49,680
Good girl.

394
00:58:49,960 --> 00:58:51,160
Let’s go, Princess.

395
00:59:18,660 --> 00:59:20,150
What’s all this?

396
00:59:21,130 --> 00:59:23,600
These kids just want to know you.

397
00:59:29,400 --> 00:59:30,400
Are you hungry?

398
00:59:32,730 --> 00:59:34,210
Close your eyes first.

399
00:59:35,460 --> 00:59:37,080
Fooling around again?

400
00:59:37,600 --> 00:59:38,950
Please close your eyes.

401
01:00:20,530 --> 01:00:21,680
Thank you.

402
01:00:25,200 --> 01:00:29,080
In my eyes, you’ll always be my princess.

403
01:00:31,260 --> 01:00:32,860
My princess forever.

404
01:01:03,260 --> 01:01:04,980
Please marry me.

405
01:01:06,960 --> 01:01:09,850
I’ll keep you safe for the rest of your life.

406
01:02:27,860 --> 01:02:33,410
I, Vayo Watinwanich, take you, Catherine De Laina Blew, to be my wife.

407
01:02:34,960 --> 01:02:41,080
I promise to stay true to you–to have and to hold, for better or for worse.

408
01:02:52,010 --> 01:02:58,450
I, Catherine De Laina Blew, take you, Vayo Watinwanich, to be my wife.

409
01:02:58,450 --> 01:03:06,180
I promise to stay true to you–to have and to hold, for better or for worse.

410
01:03:06,850 --> 01:03:12,810
And to love and respect you, until death do us apart.

411
01:05:54,330 --> 01:05:55,780
Are you nervous?

412
01:05:57,930 --> 01:05:58,730
Just a little.

413
01:06:00,260 --> 01:06:02,710
I thought you said you dated many girls before.

414
01:06:04,410 --> 01:06:07,480
Well, I’m quite reserved when it comes to that thing.

415
01:06:08,400 --> 01:06:10,380
My virtue is well guarded.

416
01:06:10,500 --> 01:06:13,010
I’m keeping it for you only.

417
01:06:14,560 --> 01:06:15,950
Unbelievable.

418
01:06:16,660 --> 01:06:17,460
It’s true.

419
01:07:01,800 --> 01:07:03,500
There’s one thing I want you to know.

420
01:07:06,260 --> 01:07:07,060
Yes?

421
01:07:08,000 --> 01:07:13,180
Whatever is mine…will only be mine.

422
01:07:14,900 --> 01:07:16,350
Then…

423
01:14:02,960 --> 01:14:05,180
Here you go, it’s your favourite.

424
01:14:06,500 --> 01:14:09,460
Three pieces. If you finish them all, you might get diabetes.

425
01:14:09,730 --> 01:14:10,700
I already have it.

426
01:14:11,200 --> 01:14:12,780
I’m home.

427
01:14:15,000 --> 01:14:17,510
Lom! Sweetie!

428
01:14:21,400 --> 01:14:24,330
Why haven’t you reached out to me at all?

429
01:14:24,730 --> 01:14:26,500
Do you know how worried I am?

430
01:14:27,500 --> 01:14:28,460
I’m sorry, Mum.

431
01:14:35,480 --> 01:14:38,910
I have someone I want to introduce to both of you.

432
01:14:39,400 --> 01:14:42,280
What? You want to introduce your girlfriend to us, huh?

433
01:14:48,700 --> 01:14:49,850
Please come in.

434
01:14:55,560 --> 01:14:56,810
Princess!

435
01:15:02,150 --> 01:15:07,850
You don’t need to do that, I’m just Blew–no longer a princess.

436
01:15:09,700 --> 01:15:11,180
What happened?

437
01:15:11,730 --> 01:15:18,050
Why is the princess with you?

438
01:15:23,530 --> 01:15:26,150
You and the princess already got married in Madelin?

439
01:15:29,930 --> 01:15:37,010
Yes, I gave up my royal title and am now a commoner.

440
01:15:37,330 --> 01:15:38,950
I’m no longer a princess.

441
01:15:41,330 --> 01:15:44,330
I’m sorry I haven’t told you earlier.

442
01:15:49,930 --> 01:15:52,150
Please don’t blame her, General Wathit.

443
01:15:55,860 --> 01:15:57,060
Not General Wathit.

444
01:16:00,930 --> 01:16:05,050
You have to call us ‘Dad’ and ‘Mum’.

445
01:16:11,700 --> 01:16:16,900
You want me to call you Dad and Mum?

446
01:16:18,930 --> 01:16:20,980
Yes, that’s right.

447
01:16:20,980 --> 01:16:24,650
You’re my daughter-in-law now, aren’t you?

448
01:16:32,060 --> 01:16:36,650
But still, what you did was wrong.

449
01:16:36,650 --> 01:16:38,310
I can’t accept it.

450
01:16:41,050 --> 01:16:46,280
But Dad, I think you already know that I love Blew.

451
01:16:46,460 --> 01:16:52,510
Yes, I do! Your mum does too.

452
01:16:52,730 --> 01:16:57,150
Who wouldn’t? You threw yourself into danger to protect her like that.

453
01:16:59,300 --> 01:17:01,100
So, what is it that you don’t approve of?

454
01:17:01,460 --> 01:17:05,310
What you did was unacceptable. How could you ignore us parents?

455
01:17:07,710 --> 01:17:11,410
Do you think you’re alone in this world? Are you an orphan or what?

456
01:17:16,500 --> 01:17:19,950
Whatever! I don’t care if you already got married in Madelin.

457
01:17:20,260 --> 01:17:22,350
The wedding must happen here too!

458
01:17:26,200 --> 01:17:27,580
Here?

459
01:17:31,160 --> 01:17:41,180
Princess–I mean, Lady Catherine.

460
01:17:43,200 --> 01:17:44,800
Please call me Blew.

461
01:17:45,060 --> 01:17:46,750
You don’t need to use royal terms with me.

462
01:17:50,060 --> 01:17:57,610
I’m going to arrange a prestigious wedding for you and Lom, Your Highness.

463
01:17:57,950 --> 01:18:00,510
Sorry, I mean–Blew.

464
01:18:03,730 --> 01:18:05,780
Thank you–Oh…

465
01:18:07,560 --> 01:18:15,950
Thank you, Dad and Mum.

466
01:18:18,900 --> 01:18:24,010
I’m so happy. Can you please say it again?

467
01:18:29,400 --> 01:18:34,710
Thank you, Dad and Mum.

468
01:18:37,300 --> 01:18:38,410
Dad, do it too.

469
01:18:41,400 --> 01:18:43,130
Okay, that’s cute.

470
01:18:49,200 --> 01:18:56,250
I’m terribly sorry I won’t be able to attend your wedding due to an urgent duty which requires my attention.

471
01:18:58,560 --> 01:19:02,310
This is a gift that Father would like to give to you.

472
01:19:08,900 --> 01:19:12,050
I think his anger has subsided by now.

473
01:19:13,200 --> 01:19:16,880
I truly wish you happiness in life.

474
01:19:17,460 --> 01:19:19,360
And I do hope we shall meet again soon.

475
01:19:20,600 --> 01:19:23,650
Father and I will always be waiting for your return.

476
01:19:55,350 --> 01:19:57,080
Cheers!

477
01:20:01,750 --> 01:20:03,310
Is it good?

478
01:20:04,710 --> 01:20:06,650
Hiyah!

479
01:20:06,650 --> 01:20:08,910
Geez!

480
01:20:09,760 --> 01:20:11,950
Can you please stop smiling?

481
01:20:11,950 --> 01:20:13,930
Isn’t this your second time getting married?

482
01:20:14,900 --> 01:20:18,650
Those who’ve never been in love would never understand, right, Din?

483
01:20:19,360 --> 01:20:23,510
True that. I also got married twice but I wasn’t as bad as you though.

484
01:20:25,700 --> 01:20:27,310
Well, I’m happy.

485
01:20:27,310 --> 01:20:32,010
Last night, I couldn’t lie on my side or else my happiness might be dripping out of my ears.

486
01:20:32,650 --> 01:20:33,810
You’re having it bad, huh?

487
01:20:34,660 --> 01:20:39,810
What’s so good about love? I don’t get it. It’s nonsense.

488
01:20:41,530 --> 01:20:44,650
Love isn’t something nonsense, Fai.

489
01:20:45,100 --> 01:20:49,550
It’s the other way round. I think love makes us see the true meaning in life

490
01:20:49,550 --> 01:20:53,980
and makes us happier than when all we did in life was work. Trust me.

491
01:20:54,530 --> 01:21:01,810
That’s right. When I lost my parents, I also lost the meaning in life–until I met Rose.

492
01:21:02,200 --> 01:21:06,110
She’s the reason I want to stay alive.

493
01:21:08,200 --> 01:21:10,380
Stop bragging about your wives, Sis.

494
01:21:11,200 --> 01:21:14,050
It’s Blew and my wedding today.

495
01:21:15,400 --> 01:21:16,600
You guys are the same.

496
01:21:16,960 --> 01:21:19,250
The more I hear it, the more I want to puke.

497
01:21:19,960 --> 01:21:24,450
I’d rather stay single for the rest of my life–be an auntie who pampers her nieces and nephews.

498
01:21:25,730 --> 01:21:26,600
Go on.

499
01:21:27,730 --> 01:21:29,050
Hey, where are you going?

500
01:21:31,000 --> 01:21:32,680
What’s wrong with her?

501
01:21:33,200 --> 01:21:36,110
Our Young Master, will she ever get married?

502
01:21:36,600 --> 01:21:38,200
Fat chance, I guess.

503
01:21:39,100 --> 01:21:41,410
Love is something she hates to her guts.

504
01:21:42,860 --> 01:21:43,900
But who knows.

505
01:21:44,160 --> 01:21:48,710
If she happens to find a good love, I don’t think she’ll be able to deny it.

506
01:21:49,700 --> 01:21:50,850
I hope so.

507
01:21:52,310 --> 01:21:53,050
Come.

508
01:21:55,660 --> 01:21:56,810
You sure take time to dress up.

509
01:21:57,750 --> 01:21:59,680
Yeah, two hours.

510
01:21:59,700 --> 01:22:00,850
- Wow.
- I knew it.

511
01:22:00,860 --> 01:22:01,880
Picking what shoes to wear.

512
01:22:54,760 --> 01:22:55,930
You too, honey.

513
01:23:01,730 --> 01:23:06,910
I might be quite talkative today since I hardly get to talk when I’m home.

514
01:23:07,780 --> 01:23:12,050
My wife’s the one who does the talking. Lom probably knows it best.

515
01:23:13,060 --> 01:23:19,880
As parents, we’re so glad to welcome another daughter to our family.

516
01:23:21,160 --> 01:23:26,680
You two have been through a lot before you’d be standing here today.

517
01:23:27,250 --> 01:23:32,110
We want nothing but for you both to always love each other and be a happy family.

518
01:23:32,380 --> 01:23:35,810
At least, love each other like we do.

519
01:23:38,760 --> 01:23:42,310
I’ll let your mother speak too. I’m so happy I got to talk a lot today.

520
01:23:42,700 --> 01:23:43,880
It’s your turn now.

521
01:23:44,860 --> 01:23:54,410
Welcome to our family, dear. That’s it. Thank you.

522
01:23:55,360 --> 01:23:57,450
Thank you, Mum.

523
01:24:13,360 --> 01:24:19,480
I wish you both an everlasting love and happiness.

524
01:24:20,210 --> 01:24:26,380
Finally, it’s Miss Blew who has made our wind stop blowing.

525
01:24:28,600 --> 01:24:29,960
Love each other for a long time.

526
01:24:37,930 --> 01:24:40,850
First, I’d like to say–Congratulations, Miss Blew.

527
01:24:40,850 --> 01:24:44,850
Welcome to the Watinwanich family.

528
01:24:44,850 --> 01:24:49,280
Finally, this tiger has now become toothless.

529
01:25:00,160 --> 01:25:06,410
I’m so happy that you no longer have to walk alone–you’ll always have Miss Blew by your side.

530
01:25:07,350 --> 01:25:11,250
From now on, no matter what happens, don’t ever let go of each other’s hands.

531
01:25:17,800 --> 01:25:20,480
It’s not easy at all for you to finally be together today.

532
01:25:20,480 --> 01:25:25,180
Please remember and cherish these moments for as long as you can.

533
01:25:25,750 --> 01:25:30,380
Welcome to the Watinwanich family, Miss Blew.

534
01:25:31,080 --> 01:25:32,850
Thank you.

535
01:25:39,460 --> 01:25:42,250
Congratulations to both of you.

536
01:25:42,250 --> 01:25:48,380
See? I told you it’s risky but it’s worth giving it a try.

537
01:25:48,380 --> 01:25:53,380
And here you are. Well done, Bro.

538
01:26:04,600 --> 01:26:08,450
Right, thank you so much, everyone.

539
01:26:08,450 --> 01:26:11,350
All of you here means a lot to me

540
01:26:11,810 --> 01:26:15,780
Most of all, thank you for loving me, Blew.

541
01:26:15,780 --> 01:26:29,750
I promise to love, cherish, and care for you more than my own life.

542
01:26:36,960 --> 01:26:39,510
Thank you everyone too.

543
01:26:39,850 --> 01:26:44,350
Thank you for all the love and warmth you’ve given to both of us.

544
01:26:45,660 --> 01:26:55,100
And thank you for making me realise what it’s like to love someone more than your own life.

545
01:26:56,480 --> 01:26:58,180
I love you.

546
01:26:58,180 --> 01:26:59,750
I love you.

547
01:27:41,510 --> 01:27:45,210
Throw it to me, Miss Blew! I wanna be taken! Throw it here, quick! I want to be in love!

548
01:27:45,210 --> 01:27:46,550
Throw it to me!

549
01:27:46,550 --> 01:27:50,180
Throw it to me! I want to be in love!

550
01:27:50,810 --> 01:27:53,380
Throw it to me! I want to be in love!

551
01:27:56,580 --> 01:28:00,080
Throw it to me!

552
01:28:00,080 --> 01:28:04,610
Throw it to me! I want to be in love!

553
01:28:36,480 --> 01:28:39,850
Surprise! It’s for you.

554
01:28:43,900 --> 01:28:44,610
Yes?

555
01:28:45,580 --> 01:28:48,910
I hope you’ll find your true love soon.

556
01:29:09,550 --> 01:29:15,050
Fai, we’re looking forward to welcoming our youngest sister-in-law.

557
01:29:25,530 --> 01:29:29,950
Aww, you’ll definitely get yourself a girlfriend.

558
01:29:33,610 --> 01:29:34,780
Anyone want it?

559
01:29:34,780 --> 01:29:38,080
Do you want it? Do you?

560
01:29:57,330 --> 01:30:02,580
Finally, we can be Wind and Phatpha once again.

561
01:30:04,460 --> 01:30:09,950
Says who? It’s actually Lom and Blew. We don’t need to disguise ourselves anymore.

562
01:30:12,260 --> 01:30:18,200
I can’t believe the princess of Madelin is now walking right by my side.

563
01:30:20,560 --> 01:30:26,710
Have you ever thought what brought us together when we were actually a world apart?

564
01:30:28,900 --> 01:30:30,860
Thanks to those traitors, maybe.

565
01:30:32,860 --> 01:30:33,730
No, not them.

566
01:30:35,960 --> 01:30:44,010
Then, thanks to the wind for bringing us together.

567
01:30:50,000 --> 01:30:51,100
I love you, Blew.

568
01:30:58,300 --> 01:31:00,010
I love you too, Lom.

569
01:32:55,780 --> 01:33:06,210
♫ I wonder which star it is that guided me to meet you ♫

570
